args: The convoy carrying the manacaster\nwas waylaid. The carriage driver is\nsafe, thankfully...
But the caster's gone. I get you.\nI'll help track down whoever took it.
I appreciate it. I'll make for Chanzelia to\ninform my sister of what's happened.
I would ask you to track the thief. And let\nme give you this spare caster Chelle sent,\njust in case.
I'd rather put my caster days behind me,\nbut I suppose now ain't the time to be\npicky.
Any idea where our rat might be hiding?
The convoy was ambushed just south of\nthe Egan Flats, soâ€”
Found you. Now, how's about you hand\nover the caster before things get ugly?
Wait. Miguel?! But you're...\nThat's not possible!
No, it isn't. Because Miguel is dead, Joe,\nat your filthy hands. You killed my little\nbrother!
Ramon. Miguel was the only blood I had,\nand you killed him in a ridiculous duel for\nthe right to challenge that bowmaster.
Funny. He never mentioned a brother.\nLeast of all an identical one.
Hmph. I'm not surprised. He always had a\nchip on his shoulder as the younger twin.
So now you've come to get revenge.
I'm fresh out of flowers for his grave, you\nsee. Figured he'd prefer your head anyway!
What's wrong? You forget how to pull the\ntrigger, or are you planning to just stand\nthere and accept your fate?
Well, I won't keep you waiting. The next\nbullet's going straight through your heart!
I set out after you straight from Chanzelia.\nBut forget that, Joe. Use the caster!
I know you said it was a soulless weapon,\nbut I think there's more to it than that.
You just didn't have the right opponentâ€”\nsomeone to put that fear you were missing\ninto your heart.
But now, each of you holds the same\ncaster, and the same threat of death\nhangs over your heads. Do you feel it?
Heh. Damn right I do. My blood's\npumpin' red-hot through my veins.
This duel will tell me all I need to know\nabout the caster's worth as a weapon!
Then I'll stay out of your way.
Just don't blink, or you'll miss the show.
I won't. I leave it to you, Joe.
Sorry to keep you. Let's finish this.\nQuick draw contest suit your fancy?
Suits me fine. Bow or caster,\nthere's no one quicker than me.
Who do you think taught him? He was\na genius with the bow, no question.\nBut he lacked consistency.
We were an even match, the two of us.\nI knew that once he found his form, he'd go\non to surpass me and be the world's best!
If he was in peak condition, he'd never\nhave lost to the likes of you. I'll prove that\nwhen I kill you, here and now.
Fair enough. I can tell from your opening\nvolley you're a crack shot to rival Miguel.
But are you good enough to kill ME?\nReckon you're about to find out.
In a hurry to die, are we? Fine by me.\n...We draw when the bird on that outcrop\ntakes off. Agreed?
As you like. I'm ready whenever.
(Got him! I knew I was the fastesâ€”?!)
Heh. Looks like I'm the quicker draw.
How?! I reacted before youâ€”I'm sure of it!
Don't quite know what to tell you, brother.\nProof's in the puddin'. I'm just better.
Guess if I had to say why, it'd be...\nbecause I put my soul into it.
I've lost. Kill me and get it over with.
Pass. See, I don't much cotton to taking\norders.
Sure you can afford to let me go? As long\nas I draw breath, I'll keep coming for you!
Sign me up. I'll roll out the welcome mat.\nBut next time, make it interesting. Can't\nshoot straight when you're drunk on hate.
Revenge is a dish best served cold.\nGo cool off and we can try this again.
